Key:
C   PKGBUILD comment
F   PKGBUILD field
E   Exec file

Information we need:
C name                     the official name of the package or primary tool associated with the package
C aur-package-name         if applicable, the name of the package on the aur
C aur-maintainer           if applicable, the aur maintainer
C other-projects           other projects that contain this package
C interface                the interface (T,G,TG)
F categories               the package's archtrack categories
F archtrack-package-name   the name of the archtrack package
F description              a description of the package
E exec                     how the application is executed

The package directories contain packages which have PKGBUILDs and exec files.
The exec files are combined with information from the PKGBUILD files to
generate desktop files and AUR PKGBUILD files.
